<section class="section" data-section-id="{{ section.id }}">
  <div class="warning-box" style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto 48px"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Final results depend on base condition, weather, mixing, and installation quality. For larger projects, consult a qualified installer.</div>
  <h2 class="section-title">Step-by-Step Installation</h2>
  <div class="step-list" style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto">
    <div class="step-item"><h4>Surface Preparation</h4><p>Base must be clean, dry, and structurally sound. Remove all loose material, oil, grease, and debris.</p></div>
    <div class="step-item"><h4>Weather Check</h4><p>Apply only in dry conditions with temperatures above 50°F (10°C) and no rain forecast for 24 hours.</p></div>
    <div class="step-item"><h4>Mixing</h4><p>Mix resin and hardener exactly per the provided ratio. Add decorative stone and mix thoroughly.</p></div>
    <div class="step-item"><h4>Application</h4><p>Pour mixture onto the prepared surface. Use a trowel to spread evenly to the desired thickness.</p></div>
    <div class="step-item"><h4>Curing</h4><p>Allow 24 hours before light foot traffic. Full cure may take 48–72 hours depending on temperature.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2 class="section-title">DIY vs. Professional Installation</h2>
  <div class="card-grid" style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto">
    <div class="card"><h3>Small DIY Projects</h3><p>Areas under 50 sq ft with good base conditions may be suitable for confident DIYers.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Professional Recommended</h3><p>For patios over 100 sq ft, pool decks, driveways, or commercial projects, consult a qualified installer.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

